text = "[font_size=34][b][color=3cff78]OPCODE SONATA[/color][/b][/font_size]
For Gamedev.js Jam 2026 - Theme: Machines
CHALLENGE : Open Source by GitHub

[font_size=24][b][color=3cff78]Tools[/color][/b][/font_size]
Game Engine: Godot 4.6
Software: Photoshop & Aseprite
[font_size=24][b][color=3cff78]FONTS[/color][/b][/font_size]
Pixel Highscore by Alex Hinton
Little Pixel by Ly97
[font_size=24][b][color=3cff78]MUSIC[/color][/b][/font_size]
Pachelbel - Canon in D Major ( Music by Clavier Clavier from Pixabay )
Antonio Vivaldi - Violin Concerto in E major, RV 269 'Spring' - I. Allegro
Mozart - Eine Kleine Nachtmusik / Serenade in G major
Tchaikovsky - Swan Lake ( Music by LAURENT BUCZEK from Pixabay )
Franz Schubert - Marche militaire in D, D. 733 no. 1 

[font_size=24][b][color=3cff78]Development[/color][/b][/font_size]
[font_size=20][color=3cff78]Satori[/color][/font_size] : Lead Programmer, Level Designer, Concept Artist, Game Writer
[font_size=20][color=3cff78]NG[/color][/font_size] : Programmer, Concept Artist, Game Writer

[font_size=24][b][color=3cff78]Development Transparency[/color][/b][/font_size]
Large Language Models (AI) were utilised as a general assistant for logic refactoring, clean code implementation & drafting for typing paragraphs assets and text translation. While the AI served as a technical consultant, all architectural decisions and system integrations were directed and executed by the developers.

[font_size=24][b][color=3cff78]Special Thanks[/color][/b][/font_size]
End3r, Enclave Games, and you
"
